        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When running a SELECT query through one of the PDO adapters a Zend_Db_Statement_Pdo object is returned. However if you were to extend Zend_Db_Statement_Pdo with your own class, there is presently no way tell Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Abstract to use that class for new statement objects, as it is hard coded into Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Abstract::prepare().\n\nCould we add the facility to set the class used for new statement objects?"
        },
