        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17444",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It seems as if you could simply extend the pdo adapter class with a class of your own, overriding the {{prepare()}} method, is this not the case, and if not, why?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-07T13:43:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-07T13:43:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17445",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Oh you can, and that's exactly what I've done for now. I just thought it would be beneficial to have a way to do it built right in, rather than have to extend the class yourself. Much like you can set the row class in Zend_Db_Table. This would be particularly useful if you needed to do it with more than one type of adapter.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jacksleight",
                        "name": "jacksleight",
                        "displayName": "Jack Sleight",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-07T13:51:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-07T13:51:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17446",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree that we should have such support without extending the class. I've lowered the priority to minor, however, since an easy workaround is available.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-11-07T13:58:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-11-07T13:58:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
